{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17638743","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17638743"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T18:58:22+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T18:58:22+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17731"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17731","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17731"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.76,0.04,0.12,0,0.08]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10445"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72159"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10445","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10445"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17731"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57629"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4930"},{"type":"tags","id":"4943"},{"type":"tags","id":"5219"},{"type":"tags","id":"5220"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"24390"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24391"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72159","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/72159"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThis class of drugs is best used for acute pain, chronic musculoskeletal pain, and headaches. They have both peripheral and central actions.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following classes of drugs is being described?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drugs","Antidepressants","Anticonvulsants","Cannabinoids","Opioids"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe class of drugs described is \u003Cstrong\u003Enon-steroidal anti-inflammatory drugs (NSAIDs)\u003C/strong\u003E. They are commonly used for managing acute pain, chronic musculoskeletal pain, and headaches. NSAIDs work by inhibiting cyclooxygenase enzymes, which reduces the production of prostaglandins involved in inflammation and pain. This provides both peripheral and central analgesic effects.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAntidepressants\u003C/strong\u003E - Primarily used for mood disorders, though some have analgesic properties\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAnticonvulsants\u003C/strong\u003E - Used mainly for seizure disorders and some neuropathic pain conditions\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECannabinoids\u003C/strong\u003E - Used for various conditions, including chronic pain, but not typically first-line for acute pain\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOpioids\u003C/strong\u003E - Potent analgesics used for severe pain, but with a different mechanism of action\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drugs (NSAIDs) are effective for acute pain, chronic musculoskeletal pain, and headaches.","NSAIDs have both peripheral and central mechanisms of action, inhibiting cyclooxygenase enzymes to reduce inflammation and pain."],"references":["Queremel Milani DA, Davis DD. Pain Management Medications. [Updated 2023 Jul 3]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK560692/","D\u00edaz-Gonz\u00e1lez F, S\u00e1nchez-Madrid F. NSAIDs: learning new tricks from old drugs. Eur J Immunol. 2015 Mar;45(3):679-86. doi: 10.1002/eji.201445222. Epub 2015 Jan 21. PMID: 25523026; PMCID: PMC5065088.","Bindu S, Mazumder S, Bandyopadhyay U. Non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drugs (NSAIDs) and organ damage: A current perspective. Biochem Pharmacol. 2020 Oct;180:114147. doi: 10.1016/j.bcp.2020.114147. Epub 2020 Jul 10. PMID: 32653589; PMCID: PMC7347500.","Ghlichloo I, Gerriets V. Nonsteroidal Anti-Inflammatory Drugs (NSAIDs) [Updated 2023 May 1]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK547742/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57629"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17731"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57629","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/57629"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-20T23:55:30+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-20T23:55:55+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10445"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72159"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},